230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Amit\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10605:\"<p>With dozens of features from social media embed through galleries and contact forms to complex mathematical equations display and many more &#8211; <a href=\"http://jetpack.me/\" title=\"JetPack\" target=\"_blank\">JetPack</a> offers you a great way to take your blog a few steps forward all in one click and some simple settings. <strong>The newest JetPack version just released a few days ago is compatible with WPML.</strong></p>\n<p><img class=\"alignright\" alt=\"JetPack 3 Modules\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Screen-Shot-2014-05-27-at-19.09.58-300x161.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"161\" /></p>\n<p>In this short tutorial I&#8217;ll explain how to use a few of the major features that are helpful to anyone that wants to make JetPack Multilingual. There are many features in JetPack and with the new JetPack -&gt; Modules menu the admin user can see all of them and read more on each one, you can see that here:</p>\n<p><strong>In this tutorial, you will learn how to make the new JetPack 3 multilingual with WPML.<br />\n</strong><br />\nWith dozens of features from social media embed options through galleries and contact forms to complex mathematical equations display and many more &#8211; JetPack offers you a great way to take your blog a few steps forward all in one click and some simple settings. <strong>The newest JetPack version just released a few days ago is compatible with WPML.</strong></p>\n<p>You can see a live example in the <a title=\"JetPack &amp; WPML\" href=\"http://theme-testing.wpml.org/plugin-jetpack/\">JetPack + WPML demo</a> site.<br />\nTo run a multilingual site with WPML and JetPack, you will need:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a title=\"Jetpack by WordPress.com\" href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/jetpack/\" target=\"_blank\">JetPack Plugin</a></li>\n<li>A recent version of <a title=\"Purchase WPML\" href=\"https://wpml.org/purchase/\" target=\"_blank\">WPML</a>, including the String Translation and Translation Management modules</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Getting Started</h2>\n<p>These are the main steps you need to follow to get started:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Install and activate JetPack</li>\n<li>Install and activate the WPML plugins (WPML Multilingual CMS, WPML String Translation, WPML Translation Management)</li>\n<li>Set up WPML from WPML-&gt;Languages. See our WPML <a title=\"WPML Getting Started Guide\" href=\"https://wpml.org/documentation/getting-started-guide/\">Getting Started Guide</a> for complete reference</li>\n</ul>\n<p>I&#8217;ll explain how to use a few of the major features that are helpful to anyone that wants to make JetPack Multilingual. There are many features in JetPack and with the new JetPack -&gt; Modules menu the admin user can see all of them and read more on each one, you can see that here:</p>\n<h2>JetPack Contact Forms</h2>\n<p>After you install JetPack and activate the Contact Form Module you&#8217;ll see that you have a new &#8216;Add Contact Form Button&#8217; at your edit post/page pages, when you click and add a form JetPack adds shortcodes tags that create the actual form fields, buttons etc&#8230;this is easily translated like that:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Duplicate the original post that contains the JetPack form</li>\n<li>Go to WPML-&gt; String Translation and look for the needed string for translation &#8211; filtering the plugin jetpack context (if you want you can also translate manually the needed strings in the translated page edit view)</li>\n<li>Save</li>\n</ol>\n<div id=\"attachment_408267\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Screen-Shot-2014-05-27-at-19.23.20.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-408267\" alt=\"String Translation &amp; JetPack Forms\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Screen-Shot-2014-05-27-at-19.23.20-300x92.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"92\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">String Translation &amp; JetPack Forms</p></div>\n<p>Results: as you can see the form is added to a Spanish page (named Contacto) with all the strings needed for our visitors to be used in Spanish translated properly:</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_408269\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Screen-Shot-2014-05-27-at-19.25.19.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-408269\" alt=\"JetPack Contact Form &amp; WPML\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Screen-Shot-2014-05-27-at-19.25.19-300x217.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"217\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">JetPack Contact Form &amp; WPML</p></div>\n<p>You are also able to translate the email template text sent to your visitors &#8211; so our english visitors will read an english email and our spanish visitor will enjoy a spanish written email.</p>\n<h2>Tiled Galleries</h2>\n<p>This is a powerful gallery feature that let&#8217;s you create custom image galleries from within the normal edit post page of WordPress, and now with WPML you can create different galleries per language and also translate all the text that is related to those galleries. Now let&#8217;s see how this is done. First you need to enable the Tiled Galleries module, you do this in the JetPack -&gt; Modules page, after you do that you&#8217;ll see that when you create a standard WordPress gallery you have some new custom options as to how to show these images, as you can see here:</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_408286\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Screen-Shot-2014-05-27-at-19.55.04.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-408286\" alt=\"JetPack Tiled Galleries and WPML\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Screen-Shot-2014-05-27-at-19.55.04-300x106.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"106\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">JetPack Tiled Galleries and WPML</p></div>\n<p>Now after this is done and again you duplicate the post, then click &#8216;Translate Independently&#8217; and you are set to change the images, images titles and alt texts in the secondary language&#8217;s edit post page.</p>\n<p>For the sake of this tutorial I have chosen to have rounded gallery images for english and square ones for the spanish version &#8211; please note that everything is translated including the alt texts and the captions produced by JetPack</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_408871\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Screen-Shot-2014-05-28-at-15.40.48.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-408871\" alt=\"Tiled Galleries &amp; WPML\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Screen-Shot-2014-05-28-at-15.40.48-300x235.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"235\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Tiled Galleries &amp; WPML</p></div>\n<div id=\"attachment_408863\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Screen-Shot-2014-05-28-at-15.31.46.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-408863\" alt=\"Tiled Galleries &amp; WPML\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Screen-Shot-2014-05-28-at-15.31.46-300x243.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"243\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Tiled Galleries &amp; WPML</p></div>\n<h2>Extra Sidebar Widgets</h2>\n<p>This very nice module gives us many extremely useful widgets that we can add to our site among others: a Twitter widget, a Facebook like box widget, a custom image gallery widget, Upcoming Events Widget, and more. All of them can be translated to all of the site&#8217;s languages using WPML. Let&#8217;s for example look at the Tiled Gallery widget, this widget displays a photo gallery or slideshow and is related to the Tiled Gallery Module which we have activated before. To make this widget show on front page, as with any widget you need to drag it to your theme&#8217;s widget area, and then set it to have images and other related features as you can see:</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_408878\" style=\"width: 297px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Screen-Shot-2014-05-28-at-15.50.34.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-408878\" alt=\"JetPack widget gallery and WPML\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Screen-Shot-2014-05-28-at-15.50.34-287x300.png\" width=\"287\" height=\"300\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">JetPack widget gallery and WPML</p></div>\n<p>Now you can translate all texts linked to the images as explained before using WPML -&gt; String Translation, you can see here the two different language versions on the widgetized area:</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_408884\" style=\"width: 235px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Screen-Shot-2014-05-28-at-15.56.38.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-408884\" alt=\"Widget Gallery JetPack &amp; WPML\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Screen-Shot-2014-05-28-at-15.56.38.png\" width=\"225\" height=\"161\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Widget Gallery JetPack &amp; WPML</p></div>\n<div id=\"attachment_408885\" style=\"width: 227px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Screen-Shot-2014-05-28-at-15.56.29.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-408885\" alt=\"Widget Gallery JetPack &amp; WPML\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Screen-Shot-2014-05-28-at-15.56.29.png\" width=\"217\" height=\"161\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Widget Gallery JetPack &amp; WPML</p></div>\n<p>Same process will give you perfect results in all the other Extra Sidebar Widgets module features, just for an example look at the popular Facebook Like Box, I am not going to describe all the settings &#8211; I think a few images are worth&#8230;well you know&#8230;many words&#8230;so just see here:</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_408931\" style=\"width: 258px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/FB_jetpack.jpg\"><img src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/FB_jetpack-248x300.jpg\" alt=\"Facebook like box and WPML\" width=\"248\" height=\"300\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-408931\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Facebook like box and WPML</p></div>\n<p>The JetPack package contains many more features, generally if you follow the same procedure I have shown above you&#8217;ll be able to go multilingual with all of them.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:62:\"https://wpml.org/2014/05/new-jetpack-3-0-compatible-wpml/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7: