i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11765:\"<p><strong>On Saturday, May 24th, 2014</strong>, three members of WPML team will speak in Saigon, at WordPress meetup under the heading <a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Saigon-WordPress/events/178972202/\" target=\"_blank\">‚ÄúBuilding sites with WordPress‚Äù</a>.</p>\n<p><a href=\"#andrea-sciamanna\">Andrea Sciamanna</a>, WPML lead developer, will present best practices for plugin development during his workshop. <a href=\"#amir-helzer\">Amir Helzer</a>, WPML project manager and CTO of the OnTheGoSystems¬≠ company will reveal some secrets behind successful business building around a WordPress plugin. <a href=\"#dat-hoang\">Dat Hoang</a>, WPML support member and the main meetup organizer will show how to build WordPress sites efficiently with existing themes and plugins. </p>\n<p>Additionally more than ten local Vietnamese people applied as <a href=\"#speakers\">speakers</a>. </p>\n<h2>Meetup agenda</h2>\n<p>The lectures will took place in parallel in two separate rooms. More advanced topic will be presented in developers room, more general WordPress topics &#8211; in users room.</p>\n<p>Here‚Äôs how the full meetup agenda looks like: </p>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<th>Time</th>\n<th>Users&#8217; track (room 1)</th>\n<th>Developers&#8217; track (room 2)</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>08:15-09:15</td>\n<td>Registration</td>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>09:15-09:30 </td>\n<td>Opening remarks <br /><a href=\"#dat-hoang\">Dat Hoang</a></td>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>09:30-10:15</td>\n<td>[VI] How to build WordPress sites efficiently with existing themes and plugins <br /><a href=\"#dat-hoang\">Dat Hoang</a></td>\n<td>[VI] WordPress themes from scratch. A guide how to create a theme from the beginning to the end <br /><a href=\"#man-vo\">Man Vo</a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>10:15-10:30</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Break</strong></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>10:30-11:15</td>\n<td>[VI] Developers and Customers: how we can understand each other <br /><a href=\"#phong-lam\">Phong Lam</a></td>\n<td>[EN] Best practices for plugin development: create a WordPress plugin from scratch (presentation plus workshop) &#8211; part 1. <br /><a href=\"#andrea-sciamanna\">Andrea Sciamanna</a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>11:15-12:00</td>\n<td>[VI] Using the WordPress HTML Text Widget to build some extra things <br /><a href=\"#anh-thien\">Anh Thien</a></td>\n<td>[EN] Best practices for plugin development: create a WordPress plugin from scratch (presentation plus workshop) &#8211; part 2. <br /><a href=\"#andrea-sciamanna\">Andrea Sciamanna</a>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>12:00-13:00</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Lunch</strong></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>13:00-13:45</td>\n<td>[VI] Implement WooCommerce and the real case-studies: using WooCommerce for business. <br /><a href=\"#duy-luong\">Duy Luong</a></td>\n<td>[VI] WordPress usage at Project Lana. How we leverage WordPress Multisite to serve millions of users per month. Project Lana WordPress Team\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>13:45-14:30</td>\n<td>[VI] Speed up your WordPress site in live action <br /><a href=\"#thong-tran\">Thong Tran</a></td>\n<td>[EN] Do Less Work By Securing Your WordPress Site From Hackers <br /><a href=\"#thomas-howard\">Thomas Howard</a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>14:30-14:45</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Break</strong></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>14:45-15:30</td>\n<td>[EN] How to build a business around a WordPress plugin <br /><a href=\"#amir-helzer\">Amir Helzer</a></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>15:30</td>\n<td>Networking and job interviews</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<h2 id=\"speakers\">Speakers</h2>\n<h3 id=\"dat-hoang\">Dat Hoang</h3>\n<div id=\"attachment_402722\" style=\"width: 160px\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/image07.jpg\"><img src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/image07.jpg\" alt=\"Dat Hoang\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" class=\"size-full wp-image-402722\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Dat Hoang</p></div>\n<p>WPML support team member and Saigon WordPress Meetup organizer.</p>\n<p><strong>Topic:</strong> How to build WordPress sites efficiently with existing themes and plugins </p>\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\n<h3 id=\"man-vo\">Man Vo</h3>\n<div id=\"attachment_402717\" style=\"width: 160px\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/image02.jpg\"><img src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/image02.jpg\" alt=\"Man Vo\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" class=\"size-full wp-image-402717\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Man Vo</p></div>\n<p>An official in the daylight and a developer in the night. A developer and a manager at Izwebz.com</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Saigon-WordPress/messages/boards/thread/44232392http://\" target=\"_blank\">An interview with Man [vi] </a></p>\n<p><strong>Topic:</strong> WordPress themes from scratch. A guide how to create a theme from the beginning to the end</p>\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\n<h3 id=\"phong-lam\">Phong Lam</h3>\n<div id=\"attachment_402719\" style=\"width: 160px\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/image04.jpg\"><img src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/image04.jpg\" alt=\"Phong Lam\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" class=\"size-full wp-image-402719\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Phong Lam</p></div>\n<p>A freelancer working in marketing &#8211; copywriting &#8211; designing &#038; LAMP developing.<br />\nWebsites are <a href=\"http://contentaz.com/\" target=\"_blank\">www.contentaz.com</a>  and <a href=\"http://www.cancaucom.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.cancaucom.com</a> . </p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Saigon-WordPress/messages/boards/thread/44232102\" target=\"_blank\">An interview with Phong [en]</a> </p>\n<p><strong>Topic</strong>: Developers and Customers: how we can understand each other</p>\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\n<h3 id=\"andrea-sciamanna\">Andrea Sciamanna</h3>\n<div id=\"attachment_402718\" style=\"width: 160px\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/image03.jpg\"><img src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/image03.jpg\" alt=\"Andrea Sciamanna\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" class=\"size-full wp-image-402718\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Andrea Sciamanna</p></div>\n<p>WPML Multilingual plugin lead developer</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Saigon-WordPress/messages/boards/thread/44232512\" target=\"_blank\">An interview with Andrea [en] </a></p>\n<p>Topic (presentation plus workshop): Best practices for plugin development: create a WordPress plugin from scratch </p>\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\n<h3 id=\"anh-thien\">Anh Thien</h3>\n<div id=\"attachment_402721\" style=\"width: 160px\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/image06.jpg\"><img src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/image06.jpg\" alt=\"Anh Thien\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" class=\"size-full wp-image-402721\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Anh Thien</p></div>\n<p>A WordPress Eethusiast. Works with freelance team that runs a service for Website Content Update &#038; Layout. </p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Saigon-WordPress/messages/boards/thread/44177192\" target=\"_blank\">An interview with Anh [en]</a></p>\n<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Using the WordPress HTML Text Widget to build some extra things</p>\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\n<h3 id=\"duy-luong\">Duy Luong</h3>\n<div id=\"attachment_402723\" style=\"width: 160px\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/image08.jpg\"><img src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/image08.jpg\" alt=\"Duy Luong\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" class=\"size-full wp-image-402723\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Duy Luong</p></div>\n<p>A developer doing Singapore projects. A businessman in some industries: tourism, furniture and fashion.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Saigon-WordPress/messages/boards/thread/44148182\" target=\"_blank\">An interview with Duy [vi]</a></p>\n<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Implement WooCommerce and the real case-studies: using WooCommerce for business. </p>\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\n<h3 id=\"project-lana-wordpress-team\">Project Lana WordPress Team</h3>\n<div id=\"attachment_402715\" style=\"width: 160px\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/image00.png\"><img src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/image00.png\" alt=\"Project Lana WordPress Team\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" class=\"size-full wp-image-402715\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Project Lana WordPress Team</p></div>\n<p>A team which builds execllent sites for Webtretho.com</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Saigon-WordPress/messages/boards/thread/44232232\" target=\"_blank\">An interview with the team [vi]</a></p>\n<p><strong>Topic:</strong> WordPress usage at Project Lana. How we leverage WordPress Multisite to serve millions of users per month.</p>\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\n<h3 id=\"thong-tran\">Thong Tran</h3>\n<div id=\"attachment_402720\" style=\"width: 160px\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/image05.jpg\"><img src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/image05.jpg\" alt=\"Thong Tran\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" class=\"size-full wp-image-402720\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Thong Tran</p></div>\n<p>The founder of foobla.com (Joomla) and wpbriz.com (WP Pipes) </p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Saigon-WordPress/messages/boards/thread/44229162#120389342\" target=\"_blank\">An interview with Thong [vi]</a></p>\n<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Speed up your WordPress site in live action</p>\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\n<h3 id=\"thomas-howard\">Thomas Howard</h3>\n<div id=\"attachment_402724\" style=\"width: 160px\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/image09.png\"><img src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/image09.png\" alt=\"Thomas Howard\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" class=\"size-full wp-image-402724\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Thomas Howard</p></div>\n<p>The founder of MakeWP.com, a WordPress development company providing services to businesses and agencies in the US.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Saigon-WordPress/messages/boards/thread/44232432#120394662\" target=\"_blank\">An interview with Thomas [en]</a></p>\n<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Do Less Work By Securing Your WordPress Site From Hackers </p>\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\n<h3 id=\"amir-helzer\">Amir Helzer</h3>\n<div id=\"attachment_402716\" style=\"width: 160px\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/image01.jpg\"><img src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/image01.jpg\" alt=\"Amir Helzer\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" class=\"size-full wp-image-402716\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Amir Helzer</p></div>\n<p>The founder and the CTO of OnTheGoSystems¬≠ company. With WordPress since 2007.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Saigon-WordPress/messages/boards/thread/44118342\" target=\"_blank\">An interview with Amir [en]</a></p>\n<p><strong>Topic:</strong> How to build a business around a WordPress plugin</p>\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\n<h3>Your last chance to register</h3>\n<p>If you are from Vietnam and haven‚Äôt registered so far, <a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Saigon-WordPress/\" target=\"_blank\">join now</a>! Taking part in the event is an ideal opportunity not only to broaden your WordPress knowledge but also to meet new interesting people.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:83:\"https://wpml.org/2014/05/wpml-team-attending-speaking-wordpress-meetup-saigon/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:65:\"This week compatible ‚Äì Newave, Compass, Quite Nice Booking, BWL\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:79:\"https://wpml.org/2014/05/week-compatible-newave-compass-quite-nice-booking-bwl/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:88:\"https://wpml.org/2014/05/week-compatible-newave-compass-quite-nice-booking-bwl/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Sat, 17 May 2014 12:10:22 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:22:\"Compatibility Bulletin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"http://wpml.org/?p=402176\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:327:\"Today we are happy to announce that we have another 2 themes and 2 plugins to add to our compatibility list. The themes are¬†Newave,¬†Compass, and the plugins are QNB Plugin, BWL Plugin. If you want to review the entire multilingual ready list of themes and plugins you are welcome to view it here: Multilingual Ready [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Amit\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5393:\"<p>Today we are happy to announce that we have another 2 themes and 2 plugins to add to our compatibility list. The themes are¬†<a title=\"Newave theme\" href=\"http://themeforest.net/item/newave-wordpress-responsive-one-page-parallax/6808797\">Newave</a>,¬†<a title=\"Compass\" href=\"http://themeforest.net/item/compass-multipurpose-responsive-wordpress-theme-/7422625\">Compass</a>, and the plugins are <a title=\"Quite Nice Booking plugin\" href=\"http://themes.quitenicestuff.com/docs/sohohotelwp/plugin-install.html\">QNB Plugin</a>, <a title=\"BWL plugin\" href=\"http://codecanyon.net/item/BWL-advanced-faq-manager/5007135\">BWL Plugin</a>.</p>\n<p>If you want to review the entire multilingual ready list of themes and plugins you are welcome to view it here:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a title=\"Multilingual Ready Themes \" href=\"https://wpml.org/documentation/theme-compatibility/\">Multilingual Ready Themes</a></li>\n<li><a title=\"Multilingual Ready Plugins \" href=\"https://wpml.org/documentation/plugins-compatibility/\">Multilingual Ready Plugins</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Also, if you&#8217;re a theme or a plugin author and you want to make it compatible with WPML, we welcome you and ready to help: You are welcome to contact us at <a href=\"https://wpml.org/documentation/theme-compatibility/go-global-program/\">go global program page</a>.</p>\n<p>In order to expedite the process we strongly recommend that you test your theme or plugin with our <a title=\"Achieving WPML compatibility for your themes and plugins\" href=\"https://wpml.org/documentation/support/achieving-wpml-compatibility-for-your-themes-and-plugins/\">Achieving WPML compatibility for your themes and plugins</a>. It easily tests compatibility with WPML and helps you quickly make your theme or plugin <strong>Multilingual Ready</strong>.</p>\n<div class=\"feature\">\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center\">Newave¬†theme</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><a><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-340493\" alt=\"ekho\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Newave.png\" width=\"590\" height=\"300\" /></a></p>\n<blockquote><p>Newave is the perfect one page parallax WordPress theme for corporate, agency, photography or general business. 6 Home Sections, Background Video Support, Parallax Slider, Fullscreen slider, Ultra-responsive, 4 Navigation styles, customizable backgrounds(colors,images or patterns), Font Awesome icons and many more super-awesome features to keep you busy &amp; satisfied.</p></blockquote>\n<p><a class=\"button download-button vt-p\" href=\"http://themeforest.net/item/newave-wordpress-responsive-one-page-parallax/6808797\" target=\"_blank\">Purchase Newave</a></p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"feature\">\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center\">Compass¬†theme</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><a href=\"http://themeforest.net/item/compass-multipurpose-responsive-wordpress-theme-/7422625\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-340493\" alt=\"ekho\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Compass.png\" width=\"590\" height=\"300\" /></a></p>\n<blockquote><p>Compass is a clean, modern design multipurpose wordpress theme can be used for any type of website build professional and modern websites. Control every pixel of this theme. Set your colors, background patterns, change fonts, change layouts for different pages. It comes with 4 default homepage and 5 ready-make skins, you can easy to build a site as the demo via importing the xml files. Since it is responsive, the layout will adapt to different screen sizes which will make your website be compatible with any device such as smart phones, tablets or desktop computers.</p></blockquote>\n<p><a class=\"button download-button vt-p\" href=\"http://themeforest.net/item/compass-multipurpose-responsive-wordpress-theme-/7422625\" target=\"_blank\">Purchase Compass</a></p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"feature\">\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center\">Quite Nice Booking plugin</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><a href=\"http://themes.quitenicestuff.com/docs/sohohotelwp/plugin-install.html\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-340493\" alt=\"ekho\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/QNB.png\" width=\"590\" height=\"300\" /></a></p>\n<blockquote><p>The booking/accommodation part of Soho Hotel is powered by a separate plugin named &#8220;Quite Nice Booking&#8221;.</p></blockquote>\n<p><a class=\"button download-button vt-p\" href=\"http://themes.quitenicestuff.com/docs/sohohotelwp/plugin-install.html\" target=\"_blank\">Purchase Quite Nice Booking¬†plugin</a>\n</div>\n<div class=\"feature\">\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center\">BWL Advanced FAQ Manager¬†plugin</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><a href=\"http://codecanyon.net/item/bwl-advanced-faq-manager/5007135\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-340493\" alt=\"ekho\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/BWL.png\" width=\"590\" height=\"300\" /></a></p>\n<blockquote><p>BWL Advanced FAQ Manager Plugin makes easy to create FAQ sections on your WordPress powered blog. Simply activate, add FAQ items, then display them on a post , page or as a sidebar widget by using a shortcode. Cool sorting features gives you option for sorting FAQ items according to your need.</p></blockquote>\n<p><a class=\"button download-button vt-p\" href=\"http://codecanyon.net/item/bwl-advanced-faq-manager/5007135\" target=\"_blank\">Purchase BWL Advanced FAQ Manager¬†plugin</a>\n</div>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:84:\"https://wpml.org/2014/05/week-compatible-newave-compass-quite-nice-booking-bwl/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"In-development job: what it is all about\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:47:\"https://wpml.org/2014/05/development-job-isall/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:56:\"https://wpml.org/2014/05/development-job-isall/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 12 May 2014 11:25:21 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Miscellaneous\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"http://wpml.org/?p=398266\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:403:\"Dario¬†Jazbec¬†Hrvatin,¬†from Slovenia, is the first¬†in-development tester¬†for¬†OnTheGoSystems. Dario joined us in April and became a part of the Toolset development team. His first tasks were with¬†Layouts¬†plugin, testing new code as¬†it was being written and making sure nothing went unchecked. Today Dario explains what the role of an in-development tester is and how it helps to deliver [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Agnes Bury\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9974:\"<p><strong>Dario¬†Jazbec¬†Hrvatin</strong>,¬†from Slovenia, is the first¬†<strong>in-development tester</strong>¬†for¬†<a href=\"http://www.onthegosystems.com/\" target=\"_blank\">OnTheGoSystems</a>. Dario joined us in April and became a part of the Toolset development team. His first tasks were with¬†<a href=\"http://wp-types.com/home/layouts/\" target=\"_blank\">Layouts¬†plugin</a>, testing new code as¬†it was being written and making sure nothing went unchecked. </p>\n<p>Today Dario explains what the role of an in-development tester is and how it helps to deliver products better and faster. Let us see the challenges and advantages of working in a¬†WordPress¬†plugin development company from a new team member‚Äôs perspective.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_398400\" style=\"width: 238px\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><img src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/dario.jpg\" alt=\"Dario¬†Jazbec¬†Hrvatin, the Layouts plugin in-development tester\" width=\"228\" height=\"245\" class=\"size-full wp-image-398400\" /><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Dario¬†Jazbec¬†Hrvatin, the Layouts plugin in-development tester</p></div>\n<h2>A short background</h2>\n<p>My name is Dario¬†Jazbec¬†Hrvatin. I have been a web developer for some years now and at the beginning of my career it happened that I chose¬†WordPress¬†as the main platform for developing sites (a very good decision I would say). </p>\n<p class=\"clearfix\">Like every other developer, I had¬†my set of¬†favorite¬†plugins I used for most of the projects I worked on. Two of the ones I probably used the most are¬†<a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/types/\" target=\"_blank\">Types</a>¬†(for all custom fields, taxonomies, post types, etc.) and¬†<a href=\"http://wpml.org\" target=\"_blank\">WPML</a>¬†(for multilingual sites). Therefore, when the opportunity presented itself for me to become the in-development tester for the very company that made my¬†favorite plugins, of course I was happy to jump at the opportunity.</p>\n<h2>Being an in-development tester:¬†so, what is it all about?</h2>\n<p>Being an in-development tester means that you are working with the team of plugin developers as they work on new features, reworks, bug fixes, etc., and help them track down bugs and potential issues. This allows¬†the company to go¬†live with even more polished and bug-free plugins and saves time because issues can be solved more quickly compared to answering support forum tickets. Of course, it goes without saying that user feedback remains very important.</p>\n<blockquote><p>¬†<br />\nAnother good thing is that testers can be ‚Äúa fresh pair of eyes‚Äù when working with plugins. What I also have found very helpful is my own history of dealing with clients/users. This allows me to try to think more like an average user and put myself in his/her shoes. Sometimes the users need¬†some things to be spelled out to them and this is not a bad thing at all because we want plugins to be as intuitive as possible.\n</p></blockquote>\n<p>¬†<br />\nWith this, we come to another (important) part of being an in-development tester and that is to think about the usability of the products and to suggest different ideas that you think could help improve the plugins. Even the small things like the position of a link in the menu can help make a better plugin experience for the people who use it.</p>\n<h2>Can anyone be an in-development¬†tester?</h2>\n<p>You might be wondering by now, what does the testing look like? Is it just clicking around all day? What is the prerequisite knowledge? Can anyone do it?<br />\n¬†<br />\nWell, there‚Äôs no test to test if someone can be a tester (excuse my Monkey Island¬†homage), but there are certainly some things you need to know well like working with¬†WordPress¬†and having a good knowledge of programming languages like HTML, CSS, PHP, and JavaScript. You need this knowledge so you can understand what is going on in the background¬†and report issues that are often not seen in the plugin or website‚Äôs front end.</p>\n<p>I think that your personal qualities are as important as technical skills so you need the following:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Great organizational¬†skills</strong>: There are so many possible actions¬†and permutations of those actions that can be done with our plugins that it is easy to get lost if unorganized. Imagine finding a nasty bug and not remembering how exactly you produced it and you cannot replicate it anymore. Therefore, in reference to one of the questions above‚Äîno, you cannot just click around and shout ‚ÄúIn your face!‚Äù when you manage to break something. <img src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\" alt=\":)\" class=\"wp-smiley\" /> </li>\n<li><strong>Concentration and attention to details</strong>: you must be focused, very thorough, and pay attention to details. Remember that plugin¬†quality is not just on the front end, but it is code-deep.</li>\n<li><strong>Friendly and calm demeanor</strong>: since you work and communicate online, it is very important to be calm (no need for panic attacks) and sincerely nice to everyone.<br />\n¬†</li>\n</ol>\n<h2>So, what does my workday actually look like?</h2>\n<p>I start my day by checking emails and assignments from my teammates. Then we have our daily meeting in which we discuss ongoing and pressing issues that need to be resolved. After the meeting, I go through the items assigned for me to test and spend most of my day thoroughly going through them.<br />\n¬†<br />\nTests are divided into different steps regarding the specific functionality. If I find a bug or notice an issue, I usually open a ‚Äúto-do‚Äù on our task management¬†pages (we use Basecamp). It is basically an assignment to fix something with comments for further explanation/discussion. This system is very important so we can all keep track of what is fixed, what needs to be fixed, and what the overall status is at any time.</p>\n<p><strong>Finally, let me briefly explain the testing process. </strong><br />\n<div id=\"attachment_398458\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/our-task-management-system.png\"><img src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/our-task-management-system-300x174.png\" alt=\"Our task-management system\" width=\"300\" height=\"174\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-398458\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Our task-management system</p></div></p>\n<p>Before testing, I update my own plugins from the development versions, since there is always something being added or fixed in the software. In addition, since cross-browser compatibility is important, I test in Chrome, Firefox, and IE. I happened to notice the other day that we all work on different setups (Mac, Linux, and Windows) and I like this diversity; there are no OS-fanboy-wars in our meetings. <img src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\" alt=\":)\" class=\"wp-smiley\" /><br />\n¬†<br />\nI have a local setup (using XAMPP) and a test site on our server so when required, I can create new, clean WP installations for myself¬†with the necessary setup.</p>\n<p><div id=\"attachment_398459\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/darios-browser.png\"><img src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/darios-browser-300x174.png\" alt=\"How my browser typically looks during testing\" width=\"300\" height=\"174\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-398459\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">How my browser typically looks during testing</p></div><br />\nI open up a testing plan and go through the steps one by one. There are two things you need to be vigilant about during testing: having a browser console running so you see if errors show up there, and checking the WP debug.log all the time so you see PHP notices, warnings etc.<br />\n¬†<br />\nWhen you notice bugs and problems,¬†you have to open a ‚Äúto-do‚Äù for the developers. You have to be very precise when explaining the issues to them so they can recreate and fix the problem as quickly as possible. I often use screenshots and screen videos to explain problems more efficiently and easily. When necessary, we have a video chat and discuss things in this way.<br />\n¬†<br />\nDuring testing, there are often times when you are not sure if you encountered a bug or if the process is supposed to work in this way. In this case, I consult my teammates and¬†they explain/advise me on the issue. As issues are resolved, I always need to re-test them to make sure that the problem is indeed fixed.<br />\n¬†</p>\n<h2>Some great things about this job</h2>\n<p>That was just a simplified version of an in-development tester‚Äôs workday and there are always new assignments and things for me to learn and do. One of the best things is that as I have come to know our programmers, I have found them to be very generous, patient, and just great to have as co-workers.<br />\n¬†<br />\nIn addition, while issues and problems are being solved, everything is discussed and explained so you can learn. Finding bugs and making suggestions that you feel could make a better product is why you are here and your ideas will be appreciated.</p>\n<h2>A job for you</h2>\n<p><strong>Did you like Dario&#8217;s story?</strong> Do you agree that working with experienced developers seems to be a good opportunity for¬†you to develop your¬†WordPress¬†skills? And yes, being¬†an¬†in-development tester not only allows you to broaden your¬†WordPress knowledge in practice but can also be a great springboard to development positions.<br />\n¬†<br />\nIf you think that this work is for you, join us today. We are looking for talented people who will be part of our family.¬†More information and application details at:¬†<a href=\"https://wpml.org/home/were-hiring/\">&#8220;WordPress Developer and Support Jobs&#8221;</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:52:\"https://wpml.org/2014/05/development-job-isall/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:56:\"This week compatible ‚Äì Adams, Pytheas, Mtphr Galleries\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:71:\"https://wpml.org/2014/05/week-compatible-adams-pytheas-mtphr-galleries/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:80:\"https://wpml.org/2014/05/week-compatible-adams-pytheas-mtphr-galleries/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 09 May 2014 15:19:05 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:22:\"Compatibility Bulletin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"http://wpml.org/?p=397428\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:336:\"Today we are happy to announce that we have another 2 themes and 1 plugin to add to our compatibility list. The themes are¬†Adams,¬†Pytheas, and the plugin is Mtphr Galleries. If you want to review the entire multilingual ready list of themes and plugins you are welcome to view it here: Multilingual Ready Themes Multilingual [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Amit\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3896:\"<p>Today we are happy to announce that we have another 2 themes and 1 plugin to add to our compatibility list. The themes are¬†<a title=\"Adams theme\" href=\"http://labs.serpentsoft.com/adams-wp/en/\">Adams</a>,¬†<a title=\"Pytheas\" href=\"http://www.wpexplorer.com/pytheas-free-wordpress-theme/\">Pytheas</a>, and the plugin is <a title=\"Mtphr Galleries plugin\" href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/mtphr-galleries/\">Mtphr Galleries</a>.</p>\n<p>If you want to review the entire multilingual ready list of themes and plugins you are welcome to view it here:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a title=\"Multilingual Ready Themes \" href=\"https://wpml.org/documentation/theme-compatibility/\">Multilingual Ready Themes</a></li>\n<li><a title=\"Multilingual Ready Plugins \" href=\"https://wpml.org/documentation/plugins-compatibility/\">Multilingual Ready Plugins</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Also, if you&#8217;re a theme or a plugin author and you want to make it compatible with WPML, we welcome you and ready to help: You are welcome to contact us at <a href=\"https://wpml.org/documentation/theme-compatibility/go-global-program/\">go global program page</a>.</p>\n<p>In order to expedite the process we strongly recommend that you test your theme or plugin with our <a title=\"Achieving WPML compatibility for your themes and plugins\" href=\"https://wpml.org/documentation/support/achieving-wpml-compatibility-for-your-themes-and-plugins/\">Achieving WPML compatibility for your themes and plugins</a>. It easily tests compatibility with WPML and helps you quickly make your theme or plugin <strong>Multilingual Ready</strong>.</p>\n<div class=\"feature\">\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center\">Adams¬†theme</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><a href=\"http://labs.serpentsoft.com/adams-wp/en/\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-340493\" alt=\"ekho\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/adams.png\" width=\"590\" height=\"300\" /></a></p>\n<blockquote><p>Adams is a Responsive News, Magazine and Blog Theme, it‚Äôs built with an HTML5, Rich Snippet, CSS3, FontAwesome Vector Fonts and Twitter Bootstrap v2.3.1.</p></blockquote>\n<p><a class=\"button download-button vt-p\" href=\"http://themeforest.net/item/adams-responsive-wordpress-news-magazine-blog/5736863\" target=\"_blank\">Purchase Adams</a></p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"feature\">\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center\">Pytheas¬†theme</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><a href=\"http://www.wpexplorer.com/pytheas-free-wordpress-theme/\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-340493\" alt=\"ekho\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/pytheas.png\" width=\"590\" height=\"300\" /></a></p>\n<blockquote><p>Pytheas is a fully responsive/fluid WordPress theme for corporate, business, portfolio style websites. Built without clutter and with a minimal design its a great solution for either small websites or as a starter theme for a more ‚Äúgraphical‚Äù or elegant theme. I‚Äôve tried to keep the options to a minimal which still providing some flexibility, you‚Äôll notice things like the WordPress custom background, custom header and menu system are all supported by the theme.</p></blockquote>\n<p><a class=\"button download-button vt-p\" href=\"http://www.wpexplorer.com/pytheas-free-wordpress-theme/\" target=\"_blank\">Download Pytheas</a></p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"feature\">\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center\">Metaphor Galleries¬†plugin</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><a href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/mtphr-galleries/\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-340493\" alt=\"ekho\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/metaphor.png\" width=\"590\" height=\"300\" /></a></p>\n<blockquote><p>Creates a custom gallery post type to display your photos and videos.</p></blockquote>\n<p><a class=\"button download-button vt-p\" href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/mtphr-galleries/\" target=\"_blank\">Get Metaphor Galleries¬†plugin</a>\n</div>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:76:\"https://wpml.org/2014/05/week-compatible-adams-pytheas-mtphr-galleries/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:4:\"href\";s:22:\"https://wpml.org/feed/\";s:3:\"rel\";s:4:\"self\";s:4:\"type\";s:19:\"application/rss+xml\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:44:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\";a:2:{s:12:\"updatePeriod\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"hourly\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:15:\"up