INSERT INTO `wp_postmeta` (`meta_id`, `post_id`, `meta_key`, `meta_value`) VALUES
(1187, 132, 'titre_mission', 'Assessment Missions '),
(1188, 132, '_titre_mission', 'field_532d77e706dcf'),
(1189, 132, 'descriptif_mission', '<b>La d√©marche d‚Äô√©valuation</b> propos√©e par le Lentic est fond√©e sur le principe de l‚Äô√©valuation constructive. Loin d‚Äô√™tre v√©rificatrice, c‚Äôest-√†-dire orient√©e vers le pass√©, centr√©e sur le constat et l‚Äôobservation des faits, elle se veut r√©gulatrice et orient√©e vers le futur.¬† Elle sort du carcan de l‚Äôunique comparaison entre les objectifs et les r√©sultats (ou les entr√©es et les sorties), pour √©largir les objets d‚Äô√©valuation √† la capacit√© d‚Äôajustement des parties en pr√©sence, aux diff√©rentes √©tapes du processus, et √† la fa√ßon dont le projet a √©t√© conduit et pilot√©.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nLentic\'s <b>assessment approach</b> is grounded on the principle of constructive assessment. Far from being controlling, i.e. past-oriented and focusing on the observation and establisment of facts, the approach means to be regulatory and future-oriented. It breaks free of the mere comparison between objectives and results (or the inputs and outputs), to broaden the objects of evaluation to include the stakeholders\'s gradual ability to adjust as well as the way they have led and managed the project.\r\n\r\nBas√©e sur la r√©colte d‚Äôinformations quantitatives et qualitatives relatives aux diff√©rents niveaux d‚Äô√©valuation (national ‚Äì transnational) ainsi qu‚Äôaux divers objets √©valu√©s (objectifs, moyens pr√©vus, moyens effectifs, r√©sultats, etc.), elle est √©galement formative.¬† Gr√¢ce √† une restitution des r√©sultats et √† une appropriation des outils et grilles d‚Äô√©valuation par les √©valu√©s, elle permet d‚Äôapporter une am√©lioration en cours de projet ou lors de nouveaux projets (perfectionnement, adaptation, r√©organisation, orientation de programmes, modification d‚Äôobjectifs, choix de contenus,‚Ä¶).¬† Elle est orient√©e vers la d√©cision et suppose une capacit√© et une volont√© de remise en cause qui aboutit √† l‚Äôaugmentation de la qualit√©.\r\n\r\nBased on the collection of quantitative and qualitative data regarding the various assessment levels (national ‚Äì transnational) as well as the various objects being evaluated (objectives, possible and effective means, results, etc.), the approach is also formative. Through sharing results and making tools and evaluation grids available to those submitted to evaluation, it enables them to work on and improve an ongoing project or new ones (perfectioning, adapting, reorganizing, programme orientation, changing objectives or content choice, etc.) The approach targets decision-making and relies on a willingness to call oneself into question leading to greater quality.'),
