litative data regarding the various assessment levels (national ‚Äì transnational) as well as the various objects being evaluated (objectives, possible and effective means, results, etc.), the approach is also formative. Through sharing results and making tools and evaluation grids available to those submitted to evaluation, it enables them to work on and improve an ongoing project or new ones (perfectioning, adapting, reorganizing, programme orientation, changing objectives or content choice, etc.) The approach targets decision-making and relies on a willingness to call oneself into question leading to greater quality.'),
